\cf0 ConfigMaps\
- a resource which stores data that can be loaded into a pod\
- data can be\
	a set of key value pairs		- 		loads environment variables	[--from-literal, --from-env-file] \
	blob of text				-		JSON, XML, YAML, TOML, INI\
	binary file					-		binary data (e.g. license file)\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 - when configmap is loaded as a volume in a pod, the \'91volumeMounts:\'92 in container section specifies the directory at which the volume is attached and each data item/key becomes a file in that directory. The value of that item/key becomes the content of the file\
  it is possible to specify specific data items to load (with \'91items:\'92) as files rather than loading all the data items\
\
- if you want to change the name of the file in the container rather than using the key/item in the data section as the filename then \
  in the volumeMounts specify the name of the volume built from the configmap, add \'91subpath: <key/item name>\'92 and for mountPath specify the file name\
  volumeMounts:\
    - name: volvo\
      subpath: mykey			(this is a key in the configmap)\
      mountPath: /path/to/file\
\
