\cf0 Jobs\
- similar to replication controller\
- for one time pods\
- restartPolicy is required the pod spec\
- jobs always add a label with key \'93job-name\'94 and value as <job-name> on the pod\
- completions - how many times the job should run\
- parallelism - how many pods to run in parallel\
\
Think of it as a supervisor/controller for pods carrying out a batch process - a process that runs for a certain time to completion.\
\
jobs succeed if the process in the container returns a successful exit status else the job fails and goes into its retry policy\
\
\
\
CronJobs\
- this is a job controller, it creates jobs on a regular schedule\
- therefore includes a job spec\
- the job creates a pod as usual to do the needed work\
- cronjobs can be suspended\
- no automatic clean up for the jobs and pods that were created\
- cronjobs don\'92t add labels on jobs the way jobs do on pods, so either add your own OR use a jsonpath query \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

