What are operators: \
- a method of packaging, deploying and managing a Kubernetes application\
\
Why do we need operators:\
- an operator can install its application\
- an operator monitors its application as it runs\
- can backup data and state for its application\
- recover its application from failure\
- upgrade the application\
- scale the application\
\
\
How:\
- a k8s operator watches a CR type (its own application as type really) and takes application specific actions\
- this helps to match the current state to the desired state\
\
\
Think of operators as custom resource + controller for that custom resource\
\
\
\
\
Operator Framework:\
 - Operator SDK\
 - Operator Lifecycle Management\
 - Operator Metering\
\
